cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of online adaptation for stereo depth estimation using deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a meta-learning approach, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of online feature alignment and meta-pre-training algorithms involves optimization techniques, which can be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves the use of deep neural networks, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of meta-learning for faster convergence can also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
